body:
Looking for a Beta

I need a beta for my new Winteriron/Stony fanfiction.

Summary:

Toni wasn’t going anywhere with him as long as she had anything to do about it.

“I was hoping to do this the easier way, but the best ones do put up the best fight at first, don’t they?”

It was the last thing she remembered before darkness overtook her.

* * *

From then on it was only agony after agony.

Until it stopped. For a moment.

But every mistake was another half an hour of agony.

Then all she knew was three commands:

She was the Assistant.

The Asset, she would fight alongside with him, protect him with her life. Support him.

Complete your missions, report back. Always do what you are told, no questions asked.

And did she thrive in her commands.

If you are interested, send me a message.

summary: Ok but every “Tony Stark is/should end as a villain” argument ignores literally the entire point of his character, especially...
body:
Ok but every “Tony Stark is/should end as a villain” argument ignores literally the entire point of his character, especially when your argument hinges on the fact that he’s rich and powerful and spoiled and therefore should be a villain

like congrats you missed the entire point. Tony is rich and powerful and spoiled and it let him live most of his life in ignorance of how his actions hurt others, and the whole point is that he had a change of heart and CHOSE to be better from then on out

the thing that makes Tony interesting as a character is THE FACT that he easily could have been a bad person. He’s a rich, white man. He could have stayed entitled and selfish and been fine. But he DIDNT. The fact that he could have so easily been a villain (like Obidiah Stane and Justin Hammer) but ISNT is like. the defining element of his character

title: The Only One
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2C9F7eY

by Schmuzz

Tony Stark has some suspicions that one of his employees in R&D is sneaking tech to his competitors. He definitely doesn’t like Deadpool, but the regenerating degenerate is reliable - so long as the price is right.

Wade Wilson has been trying to emulate Spider-Man and get out of the merc business for a few months now, and happily takes Stark up on his offer. He even gets to brag to his role model/crush about how he’s been trailing his mark, a nerdy college student named Peter Parker.
